OL,4,Cpresenter Sandy Gall dies aged 97
OL,6,FDespite becoming a news presenter in
OL,7,F1970, he continued to report first-
OL,8,Fhand, spending weeks travelling on
OL,9,Fhorseback to follow the Mujahideen in
OL,10,Ftheir guerilla war against the Soviet
OL,11,FUnion in Afghanistan.
OL,13,FAfter his retirement in 1992, he
OL,14,Ffounded and became chairman of Sandy
OL,15,FGall's Afghanistan Appeal, a charity
OL,16,Ffor disabled Afghans that helped war-
OL,17,Frelated casualties, as well as
OL,18,Fchildren in refugee camps, for nearly
OL,19,F40 years.
